18:14.256 --> 18:16.256
Oh, yeah.

18:16.324 --> 18:18.263
♪ Loves me ♪

18:18.331 --> 18:20.299
Oh, yeah, that's it, that's it.

18:20.367 --> 18:22.568
Yeah, oh.

18:25.471 --> 18:27.605
Another mess to
clean up, Mr. Spivey?

18:27.673 --> 18:29.173
You seemed to have

18:29.241 --> 18:30.708
mistaken the broom closet
for the playground,

18:30.775 --> 18:32.009
where you used to expose yourself

18:32.076 --> 18:34.744
to innocent little boys and girls.

18:34.812 --> 18:35.878
No, never the boys, Doc.

18:35.946 --> 18:37.513
I had my standards.

18:37.581 --> 18:39.682
You are utterly depraved.

18:39.750 --> 18:41.818
You've done nothing to improve yourself.

18:41.886 --> 18:42.819
No, you're wrong, Doc.

18:42.887 --> 18:44.120
I'm a new man.

18:44.188 --> 18:46.723
I used to have these disgusting urges

18:46.790 --> 18:48.357
that wouldn't quit
until I busted a nut--

18:48.425 --> 18:50.292
I mean, even in public--
but I'm not sneaking around

18:50.360 --> 18:51.995
with my pants down anymore.

18:52.062 --> 18:53.563
It was Sister Mary Eunice that asked me

18:53.631 --> 18:55.599
to come watch her flash her pussy...

18:55.667 --> 18:58.802
My aim was to give
these wasted lives purpose,

18:58.870 --> 19:00.137
meaning,

19:00.205 --> 19:01.305
and I've succeeded

19:01.373 --> 19:03.474
beyond my wildest imagination.

19:03.541 --> 19:05.342
My experiments

19:05.410 --> 19:07.578
<i>with a combination of syphilis</i>
<i>and tuberculosis</i>

19:07.646 --> 19:12.083
<i>have produced results unseen in</i>
<i>the history of medical science.</i>

19:12.150 --> 19:15.285
When they arrived here, these
patients were less than men.

19:15.353 --> 19:16.554
Now, because of me,

19:16.621 --> 19:18.857
they're more than human.

19:20.793 --> 19:22.293
Would you care to see what

19:22.361 --> 19:24.262
your benevolence has produced?

19:31.704 --> 19:34.405
Witness the next stage
of human evolution.

19:36.542 --> 19:38.042
Have you lost your mind?

19:39.445 --> 19:41.412
Why on earth would you do this?

19:41.480 --> 19:43.414
Why?

19:43.481 --> 19:45.616
When the Russians launch
their nuclear missiles,

19:45.684 --> 19:49.253
20 million Americans will
be incinerated instantly.

19:49.321 --> 19:52.824
Another 20 million will suffer
a slow, agonizing death.

19:52.892 --> 19:54.759
Natural selection would have

19:54.827 --> 19:57.763
weeded out the weak, but only
over the course of time.

19:57.830 --> 20:00.933
Whereas I have managed
to improve the species now,

20:01.000 --> 20:03.202
so that we can survive the atomic blast,

20:03.269 --> 20:05.404
live through the radiation and become

20:05.472 --> 20:06.639
dominant once again.

20:06.706 --> 20:08.407
You should be locked away.

20:08.475 --> 20:09.942
With you to keep me company?

20:10.010 --> 20:11.410
We're in this together, Father.

20:11.478 --> 20:13.145
Remember?

20:13.213 --> 20:15.347
You gave me your blessing,
along with the facility

20:15.415 --> 20:16.815
and the subjects.

20:16.883 --> 20:18.283
I cannot allow this to continue.

20:18.350 --> 20:19.884
I have to expose this
to the light of day.

20:19.952 --> 20:21.652
If you do open that window,

20:21.720 --> 20:24.389
the light will illuminate
everything in Briarcliff.

20:24.456 --> 20:27.192
And I mean everything.

20:31.931 --> 20:34.433
Yes, that's what I thought.

20:34.501 --> 20:36.235
Now, you listen to me.

20:36.303 --> 20:38.471
You and I have nothing
to fear from each other.

20:38.538 --> 20:42.708
However, we do have a threat in common.

20:42.776 --> 20:46.245
We both know where the real danger lies.

20:46.313 --> 20:48.881
Can I try that?

20:48.949 --> 20:51.384
You're too young to use a knife.
You'll cut yourself.

20:51.451 --> 20:53.886
Why'd your mother
abandon you here anyway?

20:53.954 --> 20:56.322
She's scared of me.
Really?

20:56.390 --> 20:57.724
Why?

20:57.791 --> 20:59.792
She thinks I killed Josie.

20:59.860 --> 21:01.494
Did you?

21:01.562 --> 21:03.162
No.

21:03.230 --> 21:05.098
Did so.
How do you know?

21:05.165 --> 21:06.813
I know everything.

21:08.036 --> 21:08.969
I'm the devil.

21:12.111 --> 21:14.779
She deserved it, that Josie.

21:14.847 --> 21:16.848
She was a phony little shit.

21:16.915 --> 21:19.050
She didn't even like you.

21:19.118 --> 21:21.252
She just played with you
because her mother told her to.

21:23.388 --> 21:24.955
But you're lucky, because you were born

21:25.023 --> 21:28.029
with the gift of authentic impulse.

21:28.096 --> 21:29.430
Don't ever let them kill it.

21:29.498 --> 21:30.865
I wasted so much time

21:30.933 --> 21:32.033
trying to be a good girl.

21:32.100 --> 21:33.700
All I wanted in the whole world

21:33.768 --> 21:35.736
was for people to like me.

21:35.803 --> 21:39.106
<i>Okay, okay everyone, it's time!</i>

21:39.174 --> 21:42.209
Let's all welcome Mary Eunice McKee

21:42.277 --> 21:44.912
to our annual pool event.

21:47.295 --> 21:50.352
Hey, why don't you get up on
the diving board, Mary Eunice?

21:50.472 --> 21:52.720
You're our guest of honor today.

21:52.788 --> 21:55.856
♪ Love me... ♪
Go ahead.

21:55.923 --> 21:58.358
♪ But how do I know? ♪
♪ <i>Tell me</i> ♪

21:58.426 --> 22:00.026
♪ <i>How do I know?</i> ♪
All right, everyone.

22:00.094 --> 22:01.955
On the count of three,

22:02.075 --> 22:04.630
we're all gonna drop our robes.

22:06.025 --> 22:08.092
One...

22:08.431 --> 22:12.406
two... three!

22:21.187 --> 22:23.284
I was just everyone's victim.

22:23.351 --> 22:25.953
Poor Mary Eunice.

22:28.863 --> 22:32.000
The only place I thought
I'd be safe was with God.

22:32.120 --> 22:33.167
God.

22:33.234 --> 22:34.835
You know there's no God, right?

22:34.903 --> 22:37.337
You already figured out that it's just

22:37.405 --> 22:38.705
a bunch of crap someone made up

22:38.773 --> 22:40.207
to keep you from being who you are,

22:40.274 --> 22:43.944
from doing what you really want to do.

22:44.012 --> 22:46.747
What a chump.

22:46.814 --> 22:48.348
Look where it got me.

22:48.416 --> 22:50.884
Right here, taking shit
from a mean old bitch

22:50.951 --> 22:55.021
who drinks and wears trashy red lingerie

22:55.089 --> 22:57.758
under her habit.

22:59.894 --> 23:03.163
But not for long.

23:03.231 --> 23:04.899
They're gonna lock me up in my room.

23:04.966 --> 23:08.736
I'll never be able to do
anything I want ever again.

23:08.804 --> 23:10.906
Don't be a whiner.

23:10.973 --> 23:12.741
You're smarter than they are.

23:12.809 --> 23:14.809
Don't you ever forget it.

23:14.877 --> 23:17.378
Maybe you just need to learn
how to defend yourself.

23:19.649 --> 23:21.883
<i>Fine. We'll be expecting you.</i>

23:27.056 --> 23:28.523
Monsignor.

23:29.959 --> 23:30.926
Crisis averted.

23:32.529 --> 23:33.762
I mean, she-she went off

23:33.830 --> 23:36.532
and-and left her daughter here,

23:36.600 --> 23:39.402
as if we're some kind of
personal child care facility.

23:42.473 --> 23:44.875
For heaven's sakes,

23:44.942 --> 23:48.111
what is that expression
on your face, Timothy?

23:48.179 --> 23:50.347
It seems Briarcliff's become
quite a burden for you.

23:50.415 --> 23:52.448
No, no.

23:52.516 --> 23:55.485
We just had a few, uh, difficult days,

23:55.552 --> 23:57.587
but the order has been restored...

23:57.655 --> 24:00.290
Sister, I've contacted a colleague,

24:00.357 --> 24:03.759
Father Bernard, in Pittsburgh.

24:03.827 --> 24:05.929
He's just opened a home
for wayward girls.

24:07.531 --> 24:09.132
I've recommended you highly

24:09.200 --> 24:10.901
to run it.

24:10.968 --> 24:12.736
Are you firing me?

24:12.804 --> 24:14.038
You've lost your way.

24:14.105 --> 24:15.406
You need a new beginning.

24:16.742 --> 24:18.577
You're booked on a plane

24:18.644 --> 24:22.280
out of Logan Airport,
Friday morning, 8:30 a.m.

24:24.217 --> 24:28.721
This is... this is all
about Dr. Arden, isn't it?

24:28.789 --> 24:30.589
Dr. Arden is not
the issue here!

24:30.657 --> 24:33.792
Dr. Arden is
entirely the issue here!

24:35.888 --> 24:37.582
He's turned you against me.

24:37.702 --> 24:39.133
But I was right about him.

24:39.253 --> 24:40.759
Pack up your things, Sister.

25:02.252 --> 25:05.487
Little Jenny Reynolds' mother
came by and picked her up.

25:05.555 --> 25:08.390
That's fine.

25:10.160 --> 25:12.928
Is there anything else, Sister?

25:12.996 --> 25:14.062
No, Sister.

25:14.182 --> 25:15.898
Yes, Sister.
What are you doing?

25:15.965 --> 25:17.800
I'm packing.

25:17.867 --> 25:20.336
I'm leaving Briarcliff.

25:20.403 --> 25:23.105
The monsignor, in his wisdom,

25:23.172 --> 25:28.277
has decided that my talents
would serve better elsewhere.

25:29.679 --> 25:31.346
Pittsburgh, as it turns out.

25:31.414 --> 25:33.182
Pittsburgh?

25:33.249 --> 25:35.484
No, Sister Jude,
you can't leave Briarcliff.

25:35.552 --> 25:37.353
I have no choice.

25:37.421 --> 25:39.789
But what will become of us?

25:48.098 --> 25:49.932
No, I won't leave you

25:50.000 --> 25:52.301
to the tender mercies
of Dr. Arden.

25:52.369 --> 25:55.301
There's something I can do
before I'm exiled.

25:55.368 --> 25:56.501
Go to the kitchen.

25:58.771 --> 26:02.174
The special bottle of cognac
I keep for the monsignor--

26:02.242 --> 26:05.010
bring it to me.

26:05.078 --> 26:06.979
And two very clean glasses.

26:18.257 --> 26:19.791
Thredson residence.

26:19.859 --> 26:21.259
Thank God you picked up,
Dr. Thredson.

26:21.327 --> 26:22.594
You're my one phone call.

26:22.662 --> 26:24.363
Listen, you got to help me.

26:24.431 --> 26:26.832
The cops put me in jail,
and they say they have proof

26:26.900 --> 26:28.267
I killed Alma and those other ladies.

26:28.334 --> 26:29.568
They say

26:29.636 --> 26:30.769
they have a tape of my confession.

26:36.043 --> 26:38.044
<i>I thought we had a deal.</i>

26:38.112 --> 26:39.979
I thought you said, if I say
all that stuff out loud,

26:40.047 --> 26:41.247
you'll tell the courts
I could stay at Briarcliff.

26:41.315 --> 26:42.849
No, no, Kit.

26:42.916 --> 26:46.619
I told you to say
what you believe is true.

26:46.687 --> 26:48.221
<i>I was confused.</i>

26:48.288 --> 26:49.355
Now I know the truth.

26:49.423 --> 26:51.424
Alma's not dead. Grace saw her.

26:51.491 --> 26:53.292
She told me.
Kit...

26:53.360 --> 26:55.961
you need to take responsibility
for what you did.

26:59.017 --> 27:01.094
You said you'd lie for me
so I could avoid the chair,

27:01.214 --> 27:02.568
but all you did was lie to me.

27:02.636 --> 27:03.803
How'd the cops get the tape, huh?

27:03.871 --> 27:04.904
Did you give it to them?

27:04.972 --> 27:06.005
Oh, come on.

27:07.174 --> 27:08.141
<i>I bet this was</i>

27:08.208 --> 27:09.275
your plan all along, wasn't it?

27:09.343 --> 27:10.910
You didn't want to help me.

27:10.978 --> 27:12.212
You're full of shit, and you're a liar.

27:12.279 --> 27:14.281
Stop. You stop calling me that.

27:14.348 --> 27:16.751
You're a phony, lying bastard!

27:16.818 --> 27:19.086
Stop...! Stop calling me that!

27:31.166 --> 27:32.367
He's unbelievable.

27:33.836 --> 27:36.471
He has the nerve to call me a liar,

27:36.539 --> 27:39.541
when he's the one spouting fantasies

27:39.609 --> 27:40.977
about little green men!

27:41.044 --> 27:42.612
Kit?

27:42.680 --> 27:44.380
You talk to him?

27:58.897 --> 28:00.965
Perspiration from a rise
in body temperature.

28:03.836 --> 28:05.036
Accelerated heart rate.

28:06.872 --> 28:07.872
What are you up to?

28:07.940 --> 28:08.907
Nothing.

28:16.114 --> 28:17.414
I knew it.

28:19.317 --> 28:21.251
You were gonna abandon me.

28:23.255 --> 28:24.388
Just like my mother.

28:29.495 --> 28:31.797
You're all the same.

28:31.865 --> 28:33.866
I'm not...
Shut your dirty mouth.

28:33.934 --> 28:34.867
I'm not like them.

28:34.935 --> 28:36.342
I'm not.

28:36.565 --> 28:38.571
I'm not like them.
I'm not like them.

28:38.638 --> 28:40.472
It's such a disappointment...

28:40.540 --> 28:42.208
I'm not.

28:42.275 --> 28:45.744
...when people don't
live up to expectations.

28:50.383 --> 28:54.287
Sometimes all you can do is...
end it.

29:11.539 --> 29:14.507
This is your fault.

29:14.575 --> 29:16.709
You have no one to blame but yourself.

29:16.777 --> 29:17.811
Please.

29:29.423 --> 29:32.525
♪ You don't own me ♪

29:32.592 --> 29:37.457
♪ I'm not just one of your many toys ♪

29:37.525 --> 29:40.393
♪ You don't own me ♪

29:40.461 --> 29:47.166
♪ Don't say I can't go with other boys ♪

29:47.234 --> 29:50.302
♪ And don't tell me what to do ♪

29:50.369 --> 29:54.275
♪ And don't tell me what to say ♪

29:54.343 --> 29:56.910
♪ And, please, when I go out with you ♪

29:58.779 --> 30:01.214
♪ Don't put me on display... ♪

30:08.821 --> 30:10.188
Hello.

30:10.255 --> 30:11.956
It's Sam Goodman.

30:12.023 --> 30:15.092
This is Sister Jude.

30:24.135 --> 30:26.035
Toast, Arthur.

30:27.237 --> 30:29.738
A toast to what?

30:31.240 --> 30:33.274
You won.

30:33.342 --> 30:37.077
And I've always prided myself
on my good sportsmanship.

30:45.019 --> 30:48.021
To your impressive
single-mindedness.

30:48.088 --> 30:50.356
I thought this was
supposed to be a toast.

30:51.892 --> 30:53.593
Ah, yes.

30:53.660 --> 30:55.061
We're abstaining these days, aren't we?

30:57.498 --> 30:59.799
I wouldn't dream of drinking alone.

31:06.106 --> 31:08.107
You know...

31:08.175 --> 31:10.609
there are times in life
that warrant an exception.

31:12.712 --> 31:13.612
To you.

31:15.181 --> 31:16.982
And to God's will.

31:57.656 --> 31:59.857
Yes?

31:59.925 --> 32:03.061
I'm sorry, did Sister Jude send you?

32:03.128 --> 32:05.096
She doesn't know I'm here.

32:19.236 --> 32:21.071
Mr. Goodman?

32:27.512 --> 32:29.046
Mr. Goodman?

32:29.114 --> 32:30.481
I came as fast I could.

32:30.549 --> 32:32.016
I have the glass with the fingerprints.

32:37.022 --> 32:38.856
Mr. Goodman?

32:47.433 --> 32:50.602
Hello. Hello?

32:54.073 --> 32:54.973
Huh.

33:01.248 --> 33:03.249
Oh, God.

33:03.317 --> 33:05.185
Oh, no!

33:06.621 --> 33:09.890
Oh... no...

33:09.957 --> 33:11.191
Oh, God.

33:11.258 --> 33:12.525
Oh, my God.

33:12.593 --> 33:14.260
I'll call an ambulance.

33:14.328 --> 33:15.361
Listen, listen...

33:15.429 --> 33:16.696
What?
Listen...

33:16.764 --> 33:17.964
Arden did this.

33:18.032 --> 33:19.299
No, no.

33:19.366 --> 33:21.534
Nun.
Ah... What?

33:21.602 --> 33:23.303
What? What?

33:23.371 --> 33:26.442
What did...?
A nun...

33:26.510 --> 33:28.678
A nun.
A nun...

33:28.746 --> 33:30.046
A nun?

33:30.114 --> 33:31.647
What?
One of...

33:31.715 --> 33:33.049
yours.

33:33.117 --> 33:34.550
One of... yours.

33:34.618 --> 33:38.055
Hans Grouper.

33:38.122 --> 33:39.223
You were handsome.

33:42.527 --> 33:44.695
Do you mean to tell me Sister Jude

33:44.763 --> 33:49.400
has this Israeli Sherlock Holmes
holed up in some motel?

33:49.468 --> 33:52.436
She was determined to expose you.

33:52.504 --> 33:54.705
But you don't need to worry anymore.

33:54.773 --> 33:56.874
I've taken care of everything...

33:56.942 --> 33:58.409
Hans.

33:58.477 --> 34:00.378
Don't...

34:00.445 --> 34:02.380
call me that.

34:02.447 --> 34:03.948
Ever.

34:08.120 --> 34:09.954
Are you quite sure this is all of it?

34:10.022 --> 34:11.188
No.

34:11.255 --> 34:13.357
It's not all of it.

34:13.425 --> 34:15.827
I've hidden some evidence away

34:15.895 --> 34:17.429
in case you try
and double-cross me.

34:21.132 --> 34:23.501
You must understand, these...

34:23.569 --> 34:27.005
so-called Nazi hunters
are nothing but...

34:27.072 --> 34:30.809
self-loathing,
self-seeking,

34:30.876 --> 34:33.311
money-grubbing Jews!

34:33.379 --> 34:36.746
The Catholic Church
certainly understood that.

34:36.815 --> 34:39.315
At least the Pope had
the good sense to...

34:39.384 --> 34:41.618
Arthur...
I am not a monster!

34:41.686 --> 34:43.620
I'm a visionary.

34:46.056 --> 34:51.396
Do you have any idea how
lonely a path this is?

34:51.463 --> 34:53.931
What it's like to have to
carry on your work in secret,

34:53.998 --> 34:57.135
hiding from those pious vigilantes?
Arthur!

35:00.006 --> 35:01.372
You're preaching to the converted.

35:02.808 --> 35:05.043
Why?

35:06.879 --> 35:09.148
Why are you protecting me?

35:15.021 --> 35:17.189
You're not in love with me.

35:18.525 --> 35:21.160
I'm no fool.

35:21.228 --> 35:23.163
I know I'm too old.

35:23.231 --> 35:25.333
Too ugly.

35:25.400 --> 35:28.635
Is there something...

35:28.703 --> 35:30.070
you want from me?

35:31.573 --> 35:35.175
This is the beginning
of a whole new era.

35:35.243 --> 35:38.179
All you need to do

35:38.246 --> 35:40.080
is trust me

35:40.148 --> 35:43.483
with your entire soul,

35:43.551 --> 35:46.519
and I promise you

35:46.587 --> 35:48.522
that everything will work out.

35:56.598 --> 35:58.833
Who killed her?

35:58.901 --> 36:00.468
Did you see him?

36:00.536 --> 36:02.637
He was tall.

36:02.705 --> 36:04.005
He had a beard

36:04.073 --> 36:05.840
and a brown jacket.

36:05.908 --> 36:08.744
First, he slashed my brother
and sister's throats,

36:08.812 --> 36:11.647
then he stabbed my mother in the back.

36:11.714 --> 36:13.815
I tried to stop him,

36:13.883 --> 36:15.817
but he said he would kill me, too,

36:15.885 --> 36:18.119
if I moved a muscle.

36:26.028 --> 36:28.162
You're trying not to scream.

36:29.965 --> 36:32.500
But you will.

36:35.938 --> 36:39.274
They always do
when I make the first incision.

36:40.676 --> 36:42.577
But then shock will take over...

36:44.780 --> 36:47.415
...and you won't
feel anything.

36:50.619 --> 36:53.487
It doesn't have to be this way.

36:55.324 --> 36:57.524
I wish that were true, Lana.

36:59.827 --> 37:03.195
I had such high hopes for you.

37:03.263 --> 37:05.464
From the moment

37:05.531 --> 37:08.267
I saw you, so ambitious,

37:08.335 --> 37:10.603
so... alive.

37:10.671 --> 37:12.372
I was never alive in there.

37:13.741 --> 37:16.609
No, not there.

37:16.677 --> 37:19.712
Before Briarcliff.

37:19.780 --> 37:21.180
<i>Oh, come on, Phil.</i>

37:21.248 --> 37:23.449
Aren't you sick and tired
of writing the same piece

37:23.517 --> 37:25.017
with different names?

37:25.085 --> 37:27.219
Start with some blood and guts,
a pinch of sympathy

37:27.287 --> 37:28.754
for the poor victims,

37:28.822 --> 37:30.856
and then top it off with moral outrage.

37:30.924 --> 37:32.391
Isn't that the recipe?
You're the one who knows about recipes.

37:32.459 --> 37:34.592
What are you doing here?

37:34.659 --> 37:36.160
And when did you get
assigned to the crime beat?

37:36.227 --> 37:38.595
You think Upton Sinclair
waits to be assigned a story?

37:38.663 --> 37:40.131
I'm making this my story.

37:40.198 --> 37:42.500
Oh, a woman's touch, huh?
Yes, exactly.

37:42.567 --> 37:44.502
That's what's been missing
from this story.

37:44.569 --> 37:47.037
You think this mook's just some monster,

37:47.105 --> 37:49.139
but no monster starts off that way.

37:49.207 --> 37:52.142
He was somebody's precious baby,
crying for his mommy.

37:52.210 --> 37:53.944
Here comes your precious baby now.

37:55.747 --> 37:57.147
Hey, Walker, why'd you do it?

37:57.215 --> 37:58.449
Huh?

37:58.517 --> 38:00.518
Where's the body?

38:00.586 --> 38:02.554
Come on, Walker.

38:02.621 --> 38:04.756
What, you got nothing to say?

38:06.625 --> 38:08.459
You got a statement, Walker?

38:08.527 --> 38:10.494
I thought that you

38:10.562 --> 38:12.229
were the first person

38:12.297 --> 38:14.097
who could understand.
I do.

38:14.165 --> 38:16.332
I do understand.
No.

38:16.400 --> 38:17.500
You don't.

38:22.172 --> 38:23.573
That's all right, Oliver.

38:23.640 --> 38:25.474
I don't want you to feel guilty.

38:25.542 --> 38:28.444
A mother's love is unconditional.

38:28.512 --> 38:30.747
You never had that, did you?

38:30.815 --> 38:32.282
Everyone deserves that.

38:33.718 --> 38:35.519
Even you.

38:40.493 --> 38:42.127
Baby.

38:49.435 --> 38:51.270
It's me.

38:51.337 --> 38:53.172
My baby.

39:00.614 --> 39:02.148
Baby needs colostrum.

39:16.497 --> 39:18.164
Car out front is registered

39:18.232 --> 39:20.766
to a Leo Morrison out
of Encino, California.

39:20.834 --> 39:22.334
He one of our dead
trick-or-treaters?

39:22.402 --> 39:24.471
Doubtful. Mr. Morrison's
in his early 30s.

39:24.538 --> 39:25.904
We're putting these three as teenagers.

39:25.972 --> 39:27.930
Still trying to I.D. them.

39:27.998 --> 39:29.531
Detectives!

39:29.599 --> 39:31.466
We got another one!

39:36.438 --> 39:38.505
Mr. Morrison,
I presume.

39:40.008 --> 39:42.643
All right, full search of the grounds.

39:42.711 --> 39:44.578
Let's do it before we lose daylight.

39:44.646 --> 39:46.247
We're looking for at least a body part.

39:46.315 --> 39:49.416
Chances are whoever
called this in is our perp.

40:03.030 --> 40:04.598
This is Detective John Grayson.

40:04.666 --> 40:05.673
Who is this?

40:05.793 --> 40:07.434
You know who I am.

40:07.502 --> 40:08.836
No, I don't.

